title: An Act relative to the dental licensure compact in Massachusetts

abstracts.abstract: By Mr. Mark, a petition (accompanied by bill, Senate, No. 257) of Paul W. Mark for legislation to expedite licensure and improve access to dental care by allowing states to cooperate, share information, and maintain public safety while ensuring each state retains authority over its own licensing.  Consumer Protection and Professional Licensure.

actions.description: Referred to the committee on Consumer Protection and Professional Licensure

related_entities.name: committee on Consumer Protection and Professional Licensure

actions.description: Hearing scheduled for 09/08/2025 from 10:00 AM-1:00 PM in A-2
Accompanied a study order, see S2810
